In addition, a general re-calculation of votes in all polls may take place where there is evidence that the difference between the alleged winner of the elections in question and those who received the second vote is less than or equal to one per cent, provided that at the beginning of the session there is a request from the representative of the party and/or the coalition that issued the second of those candidates.
